<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-7 col-sm-pull-5 left_align">
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <h3 class="hidden-xs"><strong>THE COMPANY</strong></h3>
  <p>AMANDA PEARL is a New York City based accessories company known for striking, sculptural, and empowering jewelry and meticulously handmade-in-Italy clutches.</p>
  <p>Founded and designed by Seattle born Amanda Pearl Brotman, the collection is inspired by her Pacific Northwest roots, with nods to the shaping influences that she continues to reference - nature, science, music, and the visual and performing arts.</p>
  <p>AMANDA PEARL expanded into Fine Jewelry for Spring/Summer 2018, introducing the Ripples collection - referencing the beauty, strength and capacity of the sea. Inspired by the feminine and fluid shapes made on the ocean bottom by waves and ripples on the surface - outlines of energy and power - the collection is meant to be worn as a reminder of a woman’s strength and power.</p>
  <p>Amanda’s designs have been seen on women of influence such as Lupita Nyong’o, Meryl Streep, Gal Gadot, Jane Fonda, and Karlie Kloss, and in publications such as Vogue, Bazaar, InStyle and WWD.</p>
  <p>AMANDA PEARL aims to bring beauty to the world beyond the realm of fashion. Always with eyes on the environment, the company produces as sustainably as possible, working with small artisanal producers, above ground diamonds, and cultured pearls - a natural resource that helps also to maintain and improve water ecology. The company also supports causes that promote education, the arts, child welfare, and conservation.</p>
</div>

